The standardised response mean (SRM), also known as the responsiveness treatment coefficient [40], was calculated as the mean change scores between baseline and 16 week follow-up divided by the standard deviation of the differences between the baseline and 16 week follow-up scores:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
